<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Parker-Hannifin (PH)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Parker-Hannifin Corporation — using actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Data updated for current TTM &middot; 10Y Treasury: 4.18%</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${priceToUse.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${revenueHistory[4] ? (revenueHistory[4].value / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${epsHistory[4] ? epsHistory[4].value.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{marginHistory[4] ? marginHistory[4].operating : 'N/A'}%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">-${(netDebt / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Debt</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — focusing on the actual cash Parker-Hannifin produces. No multiples, no vibes. Just pure cash flow discounted back to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>PH generated <strong>${fcfBase.toLocaleString()} million</strong> in free cash flow over the trailing twelve months. This is operating cash flow minus capital expenditures. Parker-Hannifin has a robust track record of converting earnings to cash.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We project FCF to grow at <strong>8% per year</strong> for the next 5 years. This reflects Parker's "Win Strategy", ongoing aerospace cyclical tailwinds, and successful integration of recent mega-acquisitions like Meggitt.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>3% forever</strong>. This is aligned with historical long-term GDP growth plus the company's pricing power in mission-critical motion and control technologies.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>9.5%</strong>. This WACC reflects a 10Y Treasury yield of 4.18%, a standard equity risk premium, and PH's stable industrial beta.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Subtract net debt, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value minus Net Debt (${netDebt.toLocaleString()}M) = Equity Value. Divide by diluted shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is highly sensitive to its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> core judgment calls.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">8.0%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Parker-Hannifin has consistently delivered high-single to low-double digit earnings growth through organic sales, margin expansion (The Win Strategy 3.0), and accretive M&A. Aerospace system backlogs provide strong visibility.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">9.5%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Based on a 10Y Treasury of 4.18%. While Parker operates in cyclical industrial markets, its aftermarket mix (approx. 50% of sales) provides immense cash flow resilience, supporting a sub-10% cost of capital.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">3.0%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        An industrial conglomerate of this size will eventually grow roughly in line with the global economy. 3% accounts for GDP growth and their ability to pass on inflation via pricing power.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

