  <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
  <h2>What This Model Doesn't Capture</h2>

  <h3>Upside risks (our number could be too low)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mega-Acquisition Synergies:</strong> Further margin expansion from the integration of Meggitt and other aerospace acquisitions could drive FCF growth above 8%.</li>
    <li><strong>Aerospace Supercycle:</strong> Commercial aerospace OEM build rates and aftermarket demand remaining elevated for longer than anticipated.</li>
    <li><strong>Margin Expansion:</strong> "The Win Strategy 3.0" consistently surprising to the upside, permanently elevating operating margins.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Downside risks (our number could be too high)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Industrial Recession:</strong> A severe global macroeconomic downturn reducing demand across their diversified industrial end-markets.</li>
    <li><strong>Debt Load:</strong> They carry substantial debt from recent acquisitions; persistently high interest rates could impact net income and FCF conversion.</li>
    <li><strong>Supply Chain Execution:</strong> Inability to secure materials for critical aerospace and defense components.</li>
  </ul>

