  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Why use a 9.5% discount rate for Parker-Hannifin?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">While the 10-year treasury is 4.18%, Parker operates in cyclical industrial sectors. However, their high mix of aftermarket revenue provides cash flow stability, balancing the risk. 9.5% represents a fair cost of equity for an established industrial titan.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Why is Net Debt subtracted instead of Cash added?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Parker-Hannifin carries more debt than cash, primarily due to large acquisitions (like Meggitt). Therefore, we calculate Net Debt (Total Debt - Cash) and subtract it from the Enterprise Value to find the value attributable solely to equity shareholders.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Is this a buy recommendation?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">No. This is an analytical framework for estimating intrinsic value based purely on cash flows. Always conduct your own due diligence.</div>
    </details>
